<br>
That being said, I have come to the anecdotal conclusion that, like having too little wisdom, you can have to much vis-a-vis tradeskills.  I haven't done a scientific study or anything, but I have noticed that my skill ups are regular and flowing if I am between 170 and 180 wisdom.  Go above or below that and I am just wasting my time.<br>
<br>
I did several tests on this and either there is some mechanic involved that penalizes you for being too smart or too dumb, or I have been the world's greatest subject of coicidence.<br>
<br>
Has anyone else noticed the skill ups pattern?  I certainly am not claiming certainty on this.  I can only go off of what I have experienced and a few conversations with others that have had similar experiences.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts? <p>Athairic of the Mooar Empire<BR>
Barbarian Shaman of the 46th Life Cycle<BR>
Member, Ordo Ursi Prismatus<BR>
Lanys T'Vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFD6A5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/bhomeofordoursiprismatus.showUserPublicProfile?gid=joursanis>Joursanis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.starpower.net/jacked.up/jesus.bmp" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFAD18>(11/13/02 10:28:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/fhomeofordoursiprismatusfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=309.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pstr-m04.ygpweb.aol.com/data2/00F/42/D8/74/07/jYp82F6tu+zFJUXUJbNjuz8Equzr20gm0073.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Wisdom Factor in Tradeskills</span><hr size=1> from EQ shaman<br>
<br>
The formula for success rate is reportedly: <br>
<br>
Success Rate = (1.15 x Skill) – (Trivial – 70) <br>
<br>
so for SoW with a skill level of 40: <br>
<br>
Success Rate = (1.15 x 40) - (37 - 70) <br>
Success Rate = (46) - (-33) <br>
Success Rate = 79% <br>
<br>
So... <br>
<br>
If you had a 40 out of 46 rate = 87% <br>
If you had a 40 out of 47 rate = 85% <br>
<br>
Either way, you did better than the norm. <br>
<br>
As your skill gets higher, trivial actually starts to mean "success". The higher the skill level and the trivial level, the more likely you will reach the 95% success rate cap. <br>
<br>
For example, a shaman with skill of 165 attempting to make port potions (trivial at 170) would have a better success rate on a NON-trivial potion than you with a skill level beyond the SoW trivial. See: <br>
<br>
Success Rate = (1.15 x 165) - (170 - 70) <br>
Success Rate = (190) - (100) <br>
Success Rate = 90% <br>
